text.tspan: (3) Alternate Position (5) PF6 has no output driver and receives the HV pulse if using PF7 as a GPIO (6)VDDIO2 fused off
* warning: this revision involved a lot of hand editing and may
contain errors. once the formatting is cleaned up I'll resume
* PC2/PC3 split into 2 lines because of poor choices by microchip
You must choose SDA.3 and SCL.3 or SDA.2 and SCL.2 together.
* The notation xxx.? means xxx on an alternate location that isn't updated here yet
* The notation SDAs.3/SCLs.3 is where the slave pins are in dual mode.
* recommend using PIN_PA0 in preference to 0 (legacy arduino pin#)
* a * is a reminder for the analog functions of port c which
is only available with MVIO fused off and VDDIO2 tied to VDD
* colors chosen somewhat arbitrarily and easy to change
* tcaroute can be used to point timera to portX[0-5]
unfortunately on this part that is at most 3 pins
